HEADWORD: Uraninite
<hw>U*ran"i*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral consisting chiefly of uranium oxide with some lead,
thorium, etc., occurring in black octahedrons, also in masses with a
pitchlike luster; pitchblende.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

